annotationA: Protein cycle; Putative transcription factor involved in the generation of biological rhythms. Activates cycling transcription of Period (PER) and Timeless (TIM) by binding to the E-box (5'-CACGTG-3') present in their promoters
annotationB: 26S proteasome regulatory complex subunit p30; Endopeptidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proteolysis; cell proliferation; mitotic spindle elongation; cellular process; proteasome-mediated ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process; ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process; mitotic spindle organization; neurogenesis
